      "content": "It is completely understandable that you feel utterly exhausted by the performance of \"being okay\" when everything feels fundamentally wrong. That sense of being frozen while the world continues is a crushing sensation, and you don't have to pretend anymore. Acknowledging that it is wrong is a huge, honest step, and perhaps the only thing you need to do right now is allow yourself to stop fighting that reality.",
      "source": "target",
